# Cache static assets aggressively. Filenames are cache-busted with a
# ?v= query string in the HTML (e.g. style.min.css?v=20260718d), so it's
# safe to let browsers/CDNs cache these for a long time: any future
# update ships under a new ?v= value and is fetched fresh automatically.
#
# Note: this file is a Netlify/Cloudflare Pages convention. GitHub Pages
# does not read _headers and does not support custom response headers,
# so this has no effect there. If mineandyourscleaning.ca is served from
# GitHub Pages, cache lifetimes need to be addressed by moving static
# assets behind a CDN (e.g. Cloudflare in front of GitHub Pages) that can
# apply these rules at the edge.

/css/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/js/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, must-revalidate
